# Package-Specific Agent Instructions Template

Use this template to create a package-specific `AGENTS.md` or `.instructions.md` file in your package directory (`src/<package>/AGENTS.md`).

This file allows you to specify rules, conventions, and constraints specific to your package that override or supplement the project-wide `AGENTS.md`.

## Example Structure

```markdown
# <Package Name> - Agent Instructions

This package implements [brief description].

## Package-Specific Rules

### Rule 1: [Topic/Guideline]
Description of the rule and why it matters for this package.

### Rule 2: [Topic/Guideline]
Description of the rule and rationale.

